 environments for recently\naccreted galaxies. Finally, we evaluate the possibility that existing and\nfuture X-ray cluster catalogs can be used in combination with optical galaxy\npositions to detect galactic coronal emission via stacking analysis. We briefly\ndiscuss the effects of additional physical processes on coronal survival, and\nwill address them in detail in future papers in this series.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 3 Mar 2015 21:00:17 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-24"}
